cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.SY, cs.ROBOTS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper primarily focuses on analyzing the sensing volume coverage of robot workspace using on-robot Time-of-Flight (ToF) sensor array rings for safe human-robot interaction. This falls under the domain of robotics, making cs.RO the most likely sub-category.
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The proposed methodology for volumetry using octrees to quantify the detection/sensing volume of the sensors involves computer vision techniques, making cs.CV a likely sub-category.
3. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper also discusses considerations for safe human-robot interaction, which falls under the domain of human-computer interaction, making cs.HC a likely sub-category.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The analysis of the sensing volume coverage of robot workspace involves studying the change in sensing volume coverage by increasing the number of sensors per ToF sensor array ring and also increasing the number of rings mounted on robot link. This falls under the domain of systems and control, making cs.SY a likely sub-category.
5. cs.ROBOTS (Robotics): This sub-category is specifically dedicated to robotics research, making it a likely sub-category for this paper.
